  "prompt": "How do you stop a Terrier/Border Collie mix from destroying your furniture?",
  "response": "Stopping a Terrier/Border Collie mix from destroying your furniture can involve a mix of training, management, and meeting their needs. Here are some steps you can take:\n\n1. **Exercise**: These breeds are known for their high energy levels. Ensure your dog is getting enough physical exercise such as walks, runs, and playtime.\n\n2. **Mental Stimulation**: Provide mental challenges through training, puzzle toys, and interactive games to keep their minds occupied.\n\n3. **Chew Toys**: Offer appropriate chew toys to redirect their chewing behavior away from furniture.\n\n4. **Training**: Use positive reinforcement training to teach commands like \"leave it\" or \"drop it.\" Reward them for chewing on their toys instead of the furniture.\n\n5. **Supervision**: When you're home, supervise your dog closely. Use baby gates or close doors to limit access to rooms with furniture you want to protect.\n\n6. **Confinement**: When you\u2019re not home, confine your dog to a safe area where they can\u2019t access furniture, such as a crate or a dog-proofed room.\n\n7. **Deterrents**: Apply pet-safe deterrent sprays to furniture. These sprays have an unpleasant taste that can discourage chewing.\n\n8. **Routine**: Establish a consistent daily routine to reduce anxiety and destructive behavior.\n\n9. **Professional Help**: If these strategies don\u2019t work, consider consulting a professional trainer or behaviorist for personalized advice.\n\nConsistency and patience are key. It may take time, but with proper management and training, your dog can learn to leave the furniture alone.",
